    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can try this:</p>\n<pre><code> Map&lt;String,String&gt; map = new HashMap&lt;&gt;();\n Map.Entry&lt;String,String&gt; entry = map.entrySet().iterator().next();\n String key = entry.getKey();\n String value = entry.getValue();\n</code></pre>\n<p>Keep in mind, <code>HashMap</code> does not guarantee the insertion order. Use a <code>LinkedHashMap</code> to keep the order intact.</p>\n<p>Eg:</p>\n<pre><code> Map&lt;String,String&gt; map = new LinkedHashMap&lt;&gt;();\n map.put(&quot;Active&quot;,&quot;33&quot;);\n map.put(&quot;Renewals Completed&quot;,&quot;3&quot;);\n map.put(&quot;Application&quot;,&quot;15&quot;);\n Map.Entry&lt;String,String&gt; entry = map.entrySet().iterator().next();\n String key= entry.getKey();\n String value=entry.getValue();\n System.out.println(key);\n System.out.println(value);\n</code></pre>\n<p>Output:</p>\n<pre><code> Active\n 33\n</code></pre>\n<p><strong>Update</strong>:\nGetting first key in <code>Java 8</code> or higher versions.</p>\n<pre><code>Optional&lt;String&gt; firstKey = map.keySet().stream().findFirst();\nif (firstKey.isPresent()) {\n    String key = firstKey.get();\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2177522,
      "reputation" : 122172,
      "user_id" : 1927832,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 49,
