    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1412665740,
    "last_edit_date" : 1412665740,
    "creation_date" : 1412665140,
    "answer_id" : 26230281,
    "question_id" : 26230225,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<blockquote>\n  <p>how can we collect the first Key \"Value\" (i.e 33)</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>By using <code>youMap.get(keyYouHave)</code>, you can get the value of it.</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>want to store the Both \"Key\" and \"Value\" in separate variable</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>Yes, you can assign that to a variable.</p>\n\n<p>Wait .........it's not over. </p>\n\n<p>If you(business logic) are depending on the order of insertions and retrieving, you are going to see weird results. Map is not ordered they won't store in an order. Please be aware of that fact. Use some alternative to preserve your order. Probably a <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/util/LinkedHashMap.html\" rel=\"nofollow\"><code>LinkedHashMap</code></a></p>\n"
  }, {
