    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>To get the \"first\" value:</p>\n\n<pre><code>map.values().toArray()[0]\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>To get the value of the \"first\" key:</p>\n\n<pre><code>map.get(map.keySet().toArray()[0])\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Note: Above code tested and works.</p>\n\n<p>I say \"first\" because HashMap entries are not ordered.</p>\n\n<p>However, a LinkedHashMap iterates its entries in the same order as they were inserted - you could use that for your map implementation if insertion order is important.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2411568,
      "reputation" : 16474,
      "user_id" : 2106516,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 91,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/b0f93169b02d92765344dd192bb498e4?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "tmarwen",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2106516/tmarwen"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1412665793,
    "last_edit_date" : 1495540026,
    "creation_date" : 1412665793,
    "answer_id" : 26230430,
    "question_id" : 26230225,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Note that you should note that your logic flow must never rely on accessing the <code>HashMap</code> elements in some order, simply put because <code>HashMap</code>s are not ordered <code>Collection</code>s and that is not what they are aimed to do. (You can read more about odered and sorter collections in <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1084146/what-is-the-difference-between-an-ordered-and-a-sorted-collection\">this post</a>).</p>\n\n<p>Back to the post, you already did half the job by loading the first element key:</p>\n\n<pre><code>Object myKey = statusName.keySet().toArray()[0];\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Just call <code>map.get(key)</code> to get the respective value:</p>\n\n<pre><code>Object myValue = statusName.get(myKey);\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
