    "body" : "<p>Java 8 way of doing,</p>\n\n<p><code>String firstKey = map.keySet().stream().findFirst().get();</code></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 4706081,
      "reputation" : 995,
      "user_id" : 3808178,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 73,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/584395753cb959db85b12607fa7c5ef7?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Maxime Claude",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3808178/maxime-claude"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1513019458,
    "last_edit_date" : 1513019458,
    "creation_date" : 1510162881,
    "answer_id" : 47186287,
    "question_id" : 26230225,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Remember that the insertion order isn't respected in a map generally speaking. Try this :</p>\n\n<pre><code>    /**\n     * Get the first element of a map. A map doesn't guarantee the insertion order\n     * @param map\n     * @param &lt;E&gt;\n     * @param &lt;K&gt;\n     * @return\n     */\n    public static &lt;E,K&gt; K getFirstKeyValue(Map&lt;E,K&gt; map){\n        K value = null;\n        if(map != null &amp;&amp; map.size() &gt; 0){\n            Map.Entry&lt;E,K&gt; entry =  map.entrySet().iterator().next();\n            if(entry != null)\n                value = entry.getValue();\n        }\n        return  value;\n    }\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>I use this only when I am sure that that <code>map.size() == 1</code> .</p>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 992738,
        "reputation" : 497,
        "user_id" : 1009540,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/cbf3266ba81e08853466f78bb92221e7?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
        "display_name" : "BarbetNL",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1009540/barbetnl"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 1,
      "creation_date" : 1657831331,
      "post_id" : 51969221,
      "comment_id" : 128910400,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "I&#39;ve noticed that if you know the map only contains 1 value, the iterator <code>keys.values().iterator().next();</code> is much faster than the <code>keys.values().stream().findFirst().get();</code> If you know the function is going to be called often, and most of the time the map will hold only one value, this might be a performance optimization."
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1139113,
      "reputation" : 20150,
      "user_id" : 1123501,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 89,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/41d62aaf8ac4b7a0971fa65a6625018c?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
